Now, we calculate the LIX using the following formula: 

LIX = (0.0188 x average number of letters per word) + (0.0009 x average number of words per sentence) 

LIX = (0.0188 x (total characters/total words)) + (0.0009 x (1/(sentences in text/total words in text)))

First, we need the average number of letters per word and the average number of words per sentence.

- Average number of letters per word: 276/62 ≈ 4.45
